36	Dress
DressHeader{<3}Details
37	Personal appearance is very important in Thailand as a measure of respect to other people .
38	You will find
39	that dressing appropriately means that you are shown more respect in return .
DressLinkedToRespect{>6}GeneralExpectationsOfWesterners
40	This translates in many ways ,
41	even sometimes lowering initial offering prices at markets .
42	While some allowance is made for the differing customs of foreigners ,
43	Thais respond more positively to well-dressed Westerners .
44	Traditionally , Thais are modest and conservative dressers .
DressAndRespect{=5}SpecificDressRules
45	At a minimum your clothes should be neat , clean , and free from holes or tears .
46	Except at the beach or at sacred sites normal western dress is acceptable for both men and women ,
CleanDressExpectation{=8}ModestDress
47	except that you should avoid clothing
48	showing a lot of skin .
49	Pants are preferable to shorts ,
PreferModesty{>9}TopsSpecific
50	blouses should have capped sleeves ,
51	and
52	if tank tops are worn ,
53	the straps should be thick
54	( i.e. , not spaghetti straps ) .
GeneralDressRules{>7}MenSpecificAttire
55	Thai men generally wear pants ,
ThaiMenPantsNorm{>8}ShortsNorms
56	and most Thais view an adult man
57	wearing shorts
58	as fairly ridiculous ;
59	shorts are primarily worn by laborers and schoolchildren .
ShortsNotCommon{>9}ShortsLength
60	Men 's shorts should be knee length or more ,
61	if worn at all .
ClothingExpectations{=6}ShoeProtocol
62	Taking off one 's shoes at temples and private homes is mandatory etiquette ,
63	and this may even be requested at some shops .
TakeShoesOffRule{=7}RecommendedShoeTypes
64	Wear shoes
65	that slip on and off easily .
66	Flip-flops , hiking sandals , and clog-type shoes are usually a good pragmatic choice
67	for traveling in Thailand ;
68	only in the most top-end establishments are shoes required .
GeneralDress{=4}SacredSitesDress
69	It is best to play it safe with wats and other sacred sites in Thailand ;
70	your dress should be unambiguously modest and cover your entire torso and most of your limbs .
71	For men , ankle-length pants are mandatory ;
72	on top , t-shirts are acceptable ,
73	though a button-front or polo shirt would be best .
MenAttireRules{=6}WomenAttireRules
74	Many recommend
75	that women wear only full length dresses and skirts ;
76	you should make sure that your clothing covers at least your shoulders and your knees
77	and some places may require that you wear ankle-length pants or skirts and long sleeved tops .
WomenAttireRules{>7}InappropriateClothesExamples
78	Shorts and sleeveless shirts are highly inappropriate ,
79	as are short skirts .
GeneralDressRulesMenWomen{=5}ForeignersVersusLocals
80	The rules are even more strict for foreign visitors ,
81	so
82	even if you see a local in shorts
83	it 's not OK for everyone .
ForeignersVersusLocals{>6}BeachNudityInappropriate
84	Topless sunbathing is common by Western women at many tourist beaches .
85	At beaches which are primarily Thai visitors however ,
86	this is not advised .
